com.navis.framework.portal

Interface IMultiThreadBatchedDomainQueryExecutor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MultiThreadBatchedDomainQueryExecutor

    public interface IMultiThreadBatchedDomainQueryExecutor
    This interface allows to execute a domain query in multithread mode with batching. The use case is to break down in a few batches fetching values from the database. Batches are based on PK pre-fetching. This allows to avoid database limitations and make transactions shorter. Multithreading should also speed up total fetching time.

    * @author Andrey Ignatenko, 4/15/2016

        This method executes given domain query in multiple threads with batching
        Parameters:
        inUc - User context
        inOutMc - Message collector. Check if hasError after calling
        inThreadGroupName - The name for the thread group. This name will be visible by tools such as JConsole. This parameter is convinient for monitoring and diagnostic
        inPkMetafieldId - PK metafield ID
        inDomainQuery - The domain query to execute
        Returns:
        List of ValueHolders including all the batches from all threads. Could be empty.
